summary: This FBI electronic communication documents the transfer of original ELSUR (Electronic Surveillance) evidence from the Washington Field Office to the Miami Field Office for permanent storage. The evidence pertains to two cases involving Jeffrey Epstein and Alfredo Rodriguez.

persons.name: Jeffrey Epstein

persons.name: Alfredo Rodriguez
persons.context: Named as the subject in case 72-MM-113327, for which ELSUR evidence is being transferred.

connections.description: Both are subjects of separate but related FBI investigations (31E-MM-108062 and 72-MM-113327) for which ELSUR evidence is being transferred together.

events.title: Transfer of ELSUR Evidence to Miami
events.description: The Washington Field Office ELSUR Unit transfers original electronic surveillance evidence to the Miami Field Office ELSUR Unit via FedEx for permanent storage.

keyFacts: Original ELSUR (electronic surveillance) evidence related to Jeffrey Epstein and Alfredo Rodriguez was transferred from the Washington Field Office to the Miami Field Office on May 15, 2025.
The transfer involved evidence for two FBI cases: 31E-MM-108062 (Epstein) and 72-MM-113327 (Rodriguez).
The evidence was shipped via FedEx with tracking number 4531 2410 2170.
The document indicates the evidence is considered part of a 'Sensitive Investigative Matter'.
Multiple barcoded items (1D1 through 1D6 for the Rodriguez case) were included in the transfer.
